<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="75" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="75">
The generic name is composed of the Latin prefix 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">stria</emphasis>
, referring to the dense striation covering most of the body and 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">stigmus</emphasis>
referring to the large stigma of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1876" class="Insecta" family="Megastigmidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Megastigmidae</taxonomicName>
. Masculine gender.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="75" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="75">
Recognized from other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1876" class="Insecta" family="Megastigmidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Megastigmidae</taxonomicName>
by having circular head shape with concentric striated sculpture on most of face (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Striastigmus bicoloratus holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B mesosoma, dorsal view C head and mesosoma, lateral view D head, frontal view E antenna, lateral view F venation G propodeum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 200 µm except for habitus (1 mm)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677673" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">1D</figureCitation>
). Toruli situated low on head with lower margin slightly above lower margin of eyes (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Striastigmus bicoloratus holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B mesosoma, dorsal view C head and mesosoma, lateral view D head, frontal view E antenna, lateral view F venation G propodeum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 200 µm except for habitus (1 mm)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677673" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">1D</figureCitation>
). Scrobes shallow, smooth and narrowly triangular, not reaching median ocellus (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Striastigmus bicoloratus holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B mesosoma, dorsal view C head and mesosoma, lateral view D head, frontal view E antenna, lateral view F venation G propodeum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 200 µm except for habitus (1 mm)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677673" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">1D</figureCitation>
). Most setation on upper face long and black, shorter and white on lower face. Gena smooth and shiny (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Striastigmus bicoloratus holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B mesosoma, dorsal view C head and mesosoma, lateral view D head, frontal view E antenna, lateral view F venation G propodeum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 200 µm except for habitus (1 mm)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677673" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">1C</figureCitation>
). Occipital carina raised, sharp, its dorsal part reaching vertex (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Striastigmus bicoloratus holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B mesosoma, dorsal view C head and mesosoma, lateral view D head, frontal view E antenna, lateral view F venation G propodeum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 200 µm except for habitus (1 mm)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677673" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">1A</figureCitation>
). Antenna slightly clavate with a conspicuous micropilosity area on last clavomere (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Striastigmus bicoloratus holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B mesosoma, dorsal view C head and mesosoma, lateral view D head, frontal view E antenna, lateral view F venation G propodeum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 200 µm except for habitus (1 mm)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677673" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">1E</figureCitation>
). Pronotum elongated, collar margined and more than half as long as mesoscutum (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Striastigmus bicoloratus holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B mesosoma, dorsal view C head and mesosoma, lateral view D head, frontal view E antenna, lateral view F venation G propodeum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 200 µm except for habitus (1 mm)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677673" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">1B</figureCitation>
). Anterior half of collar with ten transverse carinae (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Striastigmus bicoloratus holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B mesosoma, dorsal view C head and mesosoma, lateral view D head, frontal view E antenna, lateral view F venation G propodeum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 200 µm except for habitus (1 mm)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677673" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">1B</figureCitation>
). Mesoscutum coarsely cross striated (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Striastigmus bicoloratus holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B mesosoma, dorsal view C head and mesosoma, lateral view D head, frontal view E antenna, lateral view F venation G propodeum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 200 µm except for habitus (1 mm)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677673" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">1B</figureCitation>
). Mesoscutellum delimited anterolaterally from mesoscutum and axillae by broad foveate-septated scutoscutellar sulcus separating axillae (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Striastigmus bicoloratus holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B mesosoma, dorsal view C head and mesosoma, lateral view D head, frontal view E antenna, lateral view F venation G propodeum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 200 µm except for habitus (1 mm)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677673" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">1B</figureCitation>
). Frenum coarsely reticulated, extending on about half length of mesoscutellum (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Striastigmus bicoloratus holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B mesosoma, dorsal view C head and mesosoma, lateral view D head, frontal view E antenna, lateral view F venation G propodeum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 200 µm except for habitus (1 mm)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677673" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">1B</figureCitation>
). Propodeum relatively long, area between spiracles coarsely cross striated in proximal part, striate in distal part of propodeum medially turning backwards to propodeal foramen (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Striastigmus bicoloratus holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B mesosoma, dorsal view C head and mesosoma, lateral view D head, frontal view E antenna, lateral view F venation G propodeum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 200 µm except for habitus (1 mm)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677673" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">1G</figureCitation>
). Mesosoma dorsally with scarce long black setae, three long white setae laterally on pronotal collar, one on mesoscutal lateral lobe and three smaller ones on axilla along scutoscutellar suture (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Striastigmus bicoloratus holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B mesosoma, dorsal view C head and mesosoma, lateral view D head, frontal view E antenna, lateral view F venation G propodeum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 200 µm except for habitus (1 mm)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677673" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">1B</figureCitation>
). Hind coxa bare dorsally. Fore wing with marginal vein about as long as postmarginal vein, stigma enlarged, ovoid, basal vein present (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Striastigmus bicoloratus holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B mesosoma, dorsal view C head and mesosoma, lateral view D head, frontal view E antenna, lateral view F venation G propodeum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 200 µm except for habitus (1 mm)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677673" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">1F</figureCitation>
). Petiole elongated, about 0.8
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as propodeum (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Striastigmus bicoloratus holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B mesosoma, dorsal view C head and mesosoma, lateral view D head, frontal view E antenna, lateral view F venation G propodeum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 200 µm except for habitus (1 mm)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677673" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">1G</figureCitation>
). Metasoma, not including petiole, shorter than mesosoma, smooth or with traces of coriaceous sculpture laterally (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Striastigmus bicoloratus holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B mesosoma, dorsal view C head and mesosoma, lateral view D head, frontal view E antenna, lateral view F venation G propodeum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 200 µm except for habitus (1 mm)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677673" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">1A</figureCitation>
), Gt1-2 medially slightly emarginated. Ovipositor upturned and slightly longer than the entire metasoma (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Striastigmus bicoloratus holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B mesosoma, dorsal view C head and mesosoma, lateral view D head, frontal view E antenna, lateral view F venation G propodeum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 200 µm except for habitus (1 mm)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677673" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">1A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
