</bibRefCitation>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rasplus, Boehmova &amp; Jansta" authorityYear="2022" family="Megastigmidae" genus="Striastigmus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Striastigmus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Striastigmus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
goes to couplet 14 (page 120) but differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Girault" authorityYear="1915" class="Insecta" family="Torymidae" genus="Paramegastigmus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Paramegastigmus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Paramegastigmus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Girault by having oval head with concentric striated sculpture on most of face, cross striated pronotum, mesonotum and propodeum, coarsely reticulated frenum, and bicolored petiole, mesoscutellum, metanotum and legs, as well as the bicolored setae on head and mesosoma.
</paragraph>
